{"word":"G3767 - οὖν - oûn - oon - And","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">οὖν</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">oûn</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">oon</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">And</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>NA / Not Available</span>"},{"paragraph":"இவ்விதமாய், ஆகையால் - எச்சம்"},{"paragraph":"then, therefore, accordingly, consequently"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>Apparently a primary word; (adverbially) <i>certainly</i>, or (conjugationally) <i>accordingly:</i> - and (so, truly), but, now (then), so (likewise then), then, therefore, verily, wherefore.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}